    <text id="F8535T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In writing to his father, Edward McPherson expresses relief at his parents'
                    improving health.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
              
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1857">
                            <del rend="none" hand="h1"/>
                        </date>
                        <name type="place">
                            <abbr expan="Philadelphia">Phil<hi rend="super">a</hi></abbr>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>My dear Father</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I <abbr expan="received">recd.</abbr>
                    <orig reg="today">to day</orig> Lizzie's letter. It went to Harrisburg by the
                    direct mail of Saturday, but was not delivered until Monday. Mr. Wallace
                    presented it-- I am delighted to hear that you are better &amp; that Mother
                    improves. <unclear>I presume</unclear> you will soon be alone. Don't forget to
                    send for Aunt Polly-- I write hastily a line after tea, to let you know that I
                    have heard &amp; that our anxiety is relieved.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours</salute>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="underline">
                            <abbr expan="Edward">Edwd</abbr>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
